===Etymology 5===
Unclear. May be a beautified form ({{l|zh|雅化|tr=-}}) of a word meaning "cape" (compare {{zh-l|*岬}}).

Alternatively, the "Nan'an county toponymical records" ({{lang|zh|《南安縣地名志》}}), 1981, interprets the local place name {{l|zh|長福|tr=Tn̂g-hah}} as "sunburnt for a long time", and provides {{l|zh|長𣆗|tr=-}} as the original form. Compare {{zh-l|暍|tr=hahⁿ|t=to burn or dry (of the sunlight)}}.

